---
title: Satay Chicken Stir-Fry with Peanut Sauce and Broccoli over Rice
description: Chicken and broccoli over rice is a tried-and-true Asian-inspired favorite. But to get it just right, you’ve got to hone in on more than just the chicken or the broccoli—really, it’s all about the sauce, which can make or break the dish. Luckily, we’ve got a good one: we’re blending creamy peanut butter with garlic and soy, then drizzling it all over to create waves of savory flavor throughout.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/5c1154b3e3f33902aa1baa12-f9e2c74f.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/satay-chicken-stir-fry-5c1154b3e3f33902aa1baa12-0be424e7.pdf
time required: 40 minutes
cuisine: Asian
nutrition:
  calories: 630 kcal
  fat: 27 g
  saturated fat: 5 g
  carbohydrates: 65 g
  sugar: 13 g
  protein: 36 g
  fiber: 6 g
  sodium: 570 mg
author: Michelle Doll Olson
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/satay-chicken-stir-fry-5c1154b3e3f33902aa1baa12
course: main course
servings: 2
---

Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 400 degrees. Wash and dry all produce. Bring @water{3/4%cup} and @salt{pinch} to a boil in a #small pot{}. Zest @lime{1} until you have ½ tsp zest, then cut in half. Cut one half into wedges. Mince @garlic{2%cloves}. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens.

Toss @broccoli florets{8%ounce} with a drizzle of @vegetable oil{drizzle} and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch} on a #baking sheet{}. Roast until browned and tender, ~{15-20%minutes}. Once water is boiling, add @jasmine rice{1/2%cup} to #pot{}. Cover and reduce heat to a gentle simmer. Cook until tender, about ~{15%minutes}.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine @chicken breast strips{10%ounce}, half the garlic, lime zest, @soy sauce{1%tbsp} (we'll use more later), @sugar{2%tsp}, and a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{drizzle}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{} in a #large pan{} over low heat. Add scallion whites and remaining garlic. Cook, stirring, until fragrant, about ~{1%minute}. Stir in @peanut butter{1.15%ounce}, @sugar{2%tsp}, and @soy sauce{1%tsp} (you'll have a little soy sauce left over). Slowly pour in @water{1/4%cup}, stirring to combine. Turn off heat, then stir in a squeeze of lime juice. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Transfer to a #small bowl{}. Rinse and wipe out pan.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{} in same pan over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and cooked through, ~{5-6%minutes}.

> TIP: Cook chicken in batches to avoid overcrowding.

Divide rice between #plates{}, then top with broccoli and chicken. Drizzle with as much peanut sauce as you like. Garnish with scallion greens. Serve with lime wedges and any remaining sauce on the side.